{
  "analysis": "We have decoded the rodata constants successfully. Key values: sphere radius 4.0, epsilon 0.001, viewport scale 2.0, focal length 1.0, and scene constants like -5.0, -0.5, -1.0, 100.0, plus shading constants 0.2, 0.9, 0.4, -1.5. Now we need the full function disassembly to map these constants to the ray tracer logic. The second Python command output was cut off, so we need targeted extraction of trace and main.",
  "plan": "Print the full disassembly of trace and main to files, then display them in manageable chunks with line numbers. Also decode any immediate float constants in sky_color by printing its raw bytes. This will let us reconstruct the exact C code.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -n '/<trace>:/,/^$/p' /tmp/orig.asm > /tmp/trace.asm\nsed -n '/<main>:/,/^$/p' /tmp/orig.asm > /tmp/main.asm\nwc -l /tmp/trace.asm /tmp/main.asm\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat -n /tmp/trace.asm\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat -n /tmp/main.asm | head -170\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat -n /tmp/main.asm | sed -n '171,340p'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "objdump -d /app/orig | sed -n '/<sky_color>:/,/^$/p' | head -80\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}
